---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CallToAction from "@/components/CallToAction.astro";
import { site } from "@/config/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  brand={`Dominic "Dom" Conte`}
  description="Dominic 'Dom' Conte - legal-tech founder, former real-estate solicitor, and co-founder of Purple. The story of moving from practising law to building AI products lawyers actually use."
  path="/about/"
>
  <section class="container-content pt-16 sm:pt-24">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr] lg:gap-16">
      <!-- Bio -->
      <div>
        <p class="label mb-4">About</p>
        <h1 class="text-display-sm">From practising law to building it.</h1>

        <div class="prose-editorial mt-10">
          <p>
            I'm Dominic "Dom" Conte - a legal-tech founder and former
            real-estate solicitor. Today I'm {site.jobTitle.toLowerCase()} at
            <a href={site.company.url} rel="noopener" target="_blank"
              >{site.company.name}</a
            >, where we build AI products for law firms, and I write and speak
            about what it actually takes to make legal innovation stick.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've spent most of my career starting things. I co-founded my first
            company, Varsity Events, at university, then built and sold a B2B
            health-tech start-up, Fitfix.
            Law was the chapter in between: I trained at Hogan Lovells and
            practised as a real-estate solicitor at Gowling WLG - which is where
            I learned the thing that still drives the work: the gap between how
            legal services are sold and how the work actually gets done. Lawyers
            are surrounded by repetitive, high-stakes tasks that software should
            have solved years ago - and yet most of the tools aimed at them go
            unused.
          </p>
          <p>
            That gap pulled me back to building. As Chief Product Officer at
            Avail, I spent five years building an AI platform for commercial
            real-estate lawyers, taking it from inception to the majority of the
            UK's top-100 firms - and today I'm putting those lessons to work at
            Purple. Practising law first turned out to be the unfair advantage: I
            know where the work is painful, where the judgement really lives, and
            why so many "obvious" products quietly fail to land.
          </p>

          <h2>Career so far</h2>
          <dl class="space-y-6 border-l border-hairline pl-6">
            <div class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-[7rem_1fr]">
              <dt class="label pt-1">2025 - now</dt>
              <dd>
                <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Co-Founder, Purple</span>
                <span class="block text-ink/70"
                  >Legaltech build studio - taking firms from AI strategy to
                  systems they actually run.</span
                >
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-[7rem_1fr]">
              <dt class="label pt-1">2023 - now</dt>
              <dd>
                <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
                  >LegalTech Startup Mentor, LawtechUK</span
                >
                <span class="block text-ink/70"
                  >Government-backed UK legaltech body - mentoring early-stage
                  founders.</span
                >
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-[7rem_1fr]">
              <dt class="label pt-1">2019 - 2025</dt>
              <dd>
                <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
                  >Chief Product Officer, Avail</span
                >
                <span class="block text-ink/70"
                  >AI platform for commercial real-estate lawyers - growing it
                  from inception to most of the UK's top-100 firms.</span
                >
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-[7rem_1fr]">
              <dt class="label pt-1">2015 - 2019</dt>
              <dd>
                <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
                  >Senior Associate, Gowling WLG</span
                >
                <span class="block text-ink/70"
                  >International law firm - advising on commercial real-estate
                  deals.</span
                >
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-[7rem_1fr]">
              <dt class="label pt-1">2013 - 2015</dt>
              <dd>
                <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
                  >Trainee Solicitor, Hogan Lovells</span
                >
                <span class="block text-ink/70"
                  >Global law firm - training across its commercial practice
                  groups.</span
                >
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-[7rem_1fr]">
              <dt class="label pt-1">2011 - 2015</dt>
              <dd>
                <span class="font-semibold text-ink">Co-Founder, Fitfix</span>
                <span class="block text-ink/70"
                  >B2B health-tech start-up - building it from seed funding
                  through to asset sale.</span
                >
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-[7rem_1fr]">
              <dt class="label pt-1">2008 - 2011</dt>
              <dd>
                <span class="font-semibold text-ink"
                  >Co-Founder, Varsity Events</span
                >
                <span class="block text-ink/70"
                  >Events start-up - scaling it to a team of 30-plus.</span
                >
              </dd>
            </div>
          </dl>

          <h2>What I care about</h2>
          <p>
            Adoption over hype. The hard part of legal AI was never the model -
            it's changing what people actually do on a Tuesday afternoon. I care
            about narrow, real use cases; keeping a human in the loop where
            judgement matters; and being honest about what works and what
            doesn't.
          </p>

          <h2>Beyond the work</h2>
          <p>
            I'm based in {site.location}. When I'm not building, I'm usually
            writing about legal innovation, on a podcast, or on a stage talking
            about how regulated professions adopt new technology. If any of that
            overlaps with what you're working on, I'd love to hear from you.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            The technology is no longer the hard part. The hard part is the same
            as it has always been in professional services - changing what
            people actually do.
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside class="lg:pt-16">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-hairline bg-paper">
          <img
            src={site.headshot}
            alt={`Dominic "Dom" Conte - ${site.jobTitle} at ${site.company.name}`}
            width="640"
            height="800"
            class="aspect-[4/5] w-full object-cover"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>

        <dl class="mt-8 space-y-5">
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-1">Role</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink">{site.jobTitle}, {site.company.name}</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-1">Based in</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink">{site.location}</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-1">Focus</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink">Legal AI, product, adoption</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-2">Find me</dt>
            <dd class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
              <a href={site.socials.linkedin} rel="me noopener" target="_blank"
                >LinkedIn</a
              >
              <a href={site.socials.x} rel="me noopener" target="_blank">X</a>
              <a href={site.socials.github} rel="me noopener" target="_blank"
                >GitHub</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CallToAction
    title="Let's talk"
    body="Whether it's a speaking invitation, a collaboration, or a question about legal AI - my inbox is open."
    primaryHref="/contact/"
    primaryLabel="Get in touch"
    secondaryHref="/writing/"
    secondaryLabel="Read my writing"
  />
</BaseLayout>
